homeScreenBody1: The Home Screen is where the work orders will be shown. Here the user can mark orders as complete or edit them.
homeScreenBody: At the top of the Home Screen, users will see the Farming Group(s) they are assigned. Toggling between farming groups affects which work orders are returned. For example, if the choice is Spreckles, the work orders returned would be those in ranch 01 and 17. At the end of the list, there is an All option which displays all the work orders YOU have access to in one screen.
homeScreenDateBody1: The first date that is seen when the app is opened is today's date. This means all the work orders for today are shown on the screen. The user can look at the past days 50 days from today and to the future 50 days as well.
homeScreenBox: Check Box - To mark work order as completed
homeScreenWarn: Warning - Work order past scheduled date
homeScreenEdit: Edit - Edit work order, will bring up screen
homeScreenWOBody1: When a work order is not completed on the scheduled date, at the end of the day it is automatically pushed to tomorrow
addScreenBody1: The Add Screen is used to enter work orders. This screen has 4 steps, guiding the user down the screen.
addScreenBody2: Like the Home screen, the Add screen also has the user's available farming group(s) at the top of the screen. Toggling here filters the ranches that correspond to that farming group selected.
addScreenBody3: A work order that is internal uses farming functions and activities that can be completed without outside help.
addScreenExamples1: Examples of internal functions: Land Prep, Sprinkler Pipes, Irrigate
addScreenExamples2: Examples of external functions: Planting, Drip Tape, Notify PCA - Nutrien
addScreenRanch: Pick a Ranch, and if Applies, a Block
reportScreenBody1: The report screen allows the user to select a ranch and block from their selection of all their farming groups.
reportScreenSubtitle1: A status can be one of four types.
reportScreenStatus1: Green - The Work Order was completed on or before the scheduled date.
reportScreenStatus2: LightGreen - The Work Order was completed past its scheduled date.
reportScreenStatus3: Yellow - The Work Order has yet to be completed and is past its scheduled date.
reportScreenStatus4: None - The Work Order is scheduled for today or at a later date.
